rounds.event: World War II: Third day of bombing in Dresden.
births: Jack Dann, American-Australian author and poet
Douglas Hofstadter, American author and academic

rounds.event: The drilling rig Ocean Ranger sinks during a storm off the coast of Newfoundland, killing 84 workers.
Gerald Lankester Harding and Roland de Vaux begin excavations at Cave 1 of the Qumran Caves, where they will eventually discover the first seven Dead Sea Scrolls.
Serial killer Jeffrey Dahmer is sentenced in Milwaukee to 15 terms of life in prison.
deaths: William Schuman, American composer and academic

rounds.event: At the Xichang Satellite Launch Center in China, a Long March 3B rocket, carrying an Intelsat 708, veers off course and crashes into a rural village after liftoff, killing somewhere between six and 100 people.
